title: FSIS Issues Public Health Alert for Chicken Soup due to Misbranding and an Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Dec. 13, 2019 The U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) is issuing a public health alert for chicken soup products imported from Canada that were produced by Canyon Creek Soup Co. Ltd., a Canadian establishment, because the products are misbranded...
